    <div>
      <p begin="00:00:31.985" end="00:00:50.359">&#9834; [music] &#9834;</p>
      <p begin="00:00:50.359" end="00:00:52.756">- *[Woman] I think it is impossible <br/>to overestimate*</p>
      <p begin="00:00:52.756" end="00:00:55.048">*the importance of Vidal Sassoon.*</p>
      <p begin="00:00:55.048" end="00:00:56.186">- *[Man] He's probably one of the greatest,*</p>
      <p begin="00:00:56.186" end="00:00:59.853">*if not the greatest hairdresser<br/>that's ever lived.*</p>
      <p begin="00:00:59.853" end="00:01:04.909">*- [Man] With raw talent and drive <br/>and ambition and just sheer guts*</p>
      <p begin="00:01:04.909" end="00:01:07.526">*and I will not give up.*</p>
      <p begin="00:01:07.526" end="00:01:11.081">*He built something that rocked the world.*</p>
      <p begin="00:01:11.081" end="00:01:14.174">*- [Woman] It was one man <br/>with an amazing innovative idea*</p>
      <p begin="00:01:14.174" end="00:01:16.025">*that has stood the test of time.*</p>
      <p begin="00:01:16.025" end="00:01:17.702">-* [Host] Our next guest became famous*</p>
      <p begin="00:01:17.702" end="00:01:20.286">*for creating The Shape, <br/>The Five-point, The Bob,*</p>
      <p begin="00:01:20.286" end="00:01:21.951">*and the many, many more.*</p>
      <p begin="00:01:21.951" end="00:01:24.527">*- They were the styles which set him off*</p>
      <p begin="00:01:24.527" end="00:01:30.445">*on the path to creating a multimillion<br/>dollar international corporation.*</p>
      <p begin="00:01:30.445" end="00:01:33.285">*-[Man] Well, he's an international <br/>celebrity really who revolutionized*</p>
      <p begin="00:01:33.285" end="00:01:35.762">*the way women of the world<br/>looked on the outside*</p>
      <p begin="00:01:35.762" end="00:01:38.195">*and how they view themselves <br/>on the inside.*</p>
      <p begin="00:01:38.195" end="00:01:40.460">*- [Man] Vidal was completely established*</p>
      <p begin="00:01:40.460" end="00:01:44.282">*as the leading person<br/>in hair in the world.*</p>
      <p begin="00:01:44.282" end="00:01:48.659">*- [Man] Probably the biggest legacy <br/>in modern hairdressing*</p>
      <p begin="00:01:48.659" end="00:01:50.217">*is the name Vidal Sassoon.*</p>
      <p begin="00:01:50.217" end="00:01:53.196">*- [Man] He's like, I supposed, <br/>like a big deal in hairdressing.*</p>
      <p begin="00:01:53.196" end="00:01:54.953">- *[Woman] I think if you went to Japan<br/>and asked them [chuckles]*</p>
      <p begin="00:01:54.953" end="00:01:56.391">*what hairdressers do you know?*</p>
      <p begin="00:01:56.391" end="00:01:59.002">*They would say,* "Vidal Sassoon." <br/>*They would know the name.*</p>
      <p begin="00:01:59.002" end="00:02:01.558">*- [Man] It's like being a boxer<br/>in the time of Muhammad Ali*</p>
      <p begin="00:02:01.558" end="00:02:05.662">*or being a physicist <br/>and working next to Einstein*</p>
      <p begin="00:02:05.662" end="00:02:07.483">*because he was that good.*</p>
      <p begin="00:02:07.483" end="00:02:10.644">*- [Woman] We think of Sassoon, <br/>we also think liberation.*</p>
      <p begin="00:02:10.644" end="00:02:13.737">*- [Man] He just seems to exude<br/>this magic around him.*</p>
      <p begin="00:02:13.737" end="00:02:16.302">*- [Man] If I was the Queen of England, <br/>I would knight him.*</p>
      <p begin="00:02:16.302" end="00:02:18.743">*- [Man] So much of Sassoon is a myth.*</p>
      <p begin="00:02:18.743" end="00:02:23.287">*- [Man] I fought some great people <br/>in my time,but for me, he is* the person.</p>
      <p begin="00:02:23.287" end="00:02:25.120">*Yeah, he is the Messiah.*</p>
      <p begin="00:02:25.120" end="00:02:30.236">*- [Vidal Sassoon] If you don't look good,<br/>we don't look good.*</p>
      <p begin="00:02:30.236" end="00:03:12.076">&#9834; [rock music playing] &#9834;</p>
      <p begin="00:03:24.600" end="00:03:32.490">-[Vidal Sassoon] You know I'm sitting here<br/>reflecting really at 81.</p>
      <p begin="00:03:32.490" end="00:03:35.614">Who would've dreamt that<br/>sixty seven years ago,</p>
      <p begin="00:03:35.614" end="00:03:42.717">at the age of fourteen, there I was <br/>in the East End of London.</p>
      <p begin="00:03:42.717" end="00:03:44.201">A "shampoo boy."</p>
      <p begin="00:03:44.201" end="00:03:49.585">And then sitting here, <br/>over sixty years later.</p>
      <p begin="00:03:49.585" end="00:03:53.439">And I'm wondering, <br/>"How did it all happen?"</p>
      <p begin="00:03:53.439" end="00:03:56.202">How did so much adventure happen?</p>
      <p begin="00:03:56.202" end="00:04:01.067">&#9834; [music playing] &#9834;</p>
      <p begin="00:04:01.067" end="00:04:03.735">* [Vidal Sassoon] Go back all those years, <br/>you think*</p>
      <p begin="00:04:03.735" end="00:04:08.485">*the excitement, the creativity,<br/>the people you've met.*</p>
      <p begin="00:04:08.485" end="00:04:26.257">[people chatting]</p>
      <p begin="00:04:26.257" end="00:04:29.096">- [Michael Gordon] So we're gonna go ahead<br/>and start assembling the wall</p>
      <p begin="00:04:29.096" end="00:04:30.890">because Vidal is coming to see it.</p>
      <p begin="00:04:30.890" end="00:04:33.264">I've known Vidal about fifteen years</p>
      <p begin="00:04:33.264" end="00:04:35.163">and I consider him a really good friend.</p>
      <p begin="00:04:35.163" end="00:04:38.777">I've always been in the position when<br/>I was the elder talking to other people.</p>
      <p begin="00:04:38.777" end="00:04:40.867">So, having someone <br/>who you respect immensely</p>
      <p begin="00:04:40.867" end="00:04:44.502">and who has such an impact <br/>on people's lives as a friend.</p>
      <p begin="00:04:44.502" end="00:04:46.653">It's rather wonderful.</p>
      <p begin="00:04:46.653" end="00:04:49.202">*The more I got to know him,<br/>I realized we had lot in common.*</p>
      <p begin="00:04:49.202" end="00:04:52.674">*We were both hairdressers.* <br/>*That's how we started off in London.*</p>
      <p begin="00:04:52.674" end="00:04:55.907">*Both transitioned into having <br/>product companies.*</p>
      <p begin="00:04:55.907" end="00:04:58.434">*I realized that, actually,*</p>
      <p begin="00:04:58.434" end="00:05:01.434">*nobody had really recorded <br/>his achievements, his life.*</p>
      <p begin="00:05:01.434" end="00:05:06.049">*So, I thought a book<br/>was absolutely necessary.*</p>
      <p begin="00:05:06.049" end="00:05:08.228">* I felt like it was really<br/>important to capture.*</p>
      <p begin="00:05:08.228" end="00:05:11.589">*He had an impact on the world <br/>that no hairdresser has ever had.*</p>
      <p begin="00:05:11.589" end="00:05:13.339">*He changed the way women looked.*</p>
      <p begin="00:05:13.339" end="00:05:16.714">&#9834; [music playing] &#9834;</p>
      <p begin="00:05:16.714" end="00:05:19.710">*This was the way books <br/>used to be produced to magazines.*</p>
      <p begin="00:05:19.710" end="00:05:21.688">*You put them on the floor or the wall.*</p>
      <p begin="00:05:21.688" end="00:05:23.969">You did a layout.</p>
      <p begin="00:05:23.969" end="00:05:27.546">*I think he'll really be moved to see this.*</p>
      <p begin="00:05:27.546" end="00:05:31.291">*There were series of three<br/>4-hour interviews.*</p>
      <p begin="00:05:31.291" end="00:05:33.125">*Different places, different times.*</p>
      <p begin="00:05:33.125" end="00:05:37.399">*The first place we interviewed him<br/>was in his house in Beverly Hills.*</p>
      <p begin="00:05:37.399" end="00:05:49.441">[birds chirping] [water gushing]</p>
      <p begin="00:05:49.441" end="00:05:53.729">- So, you were born 1928, <br/>in Shepherds Bush?</p>
      <p begin="00:05:53.729" end="00:05:57.017">- When I was, maybe, 2 1/2 to 3 ,</p>
      <p begin="00:05:57.017" end="00:05:58.868">my mother was evicted.</p>
      <p begin="00:05:58.868" end="00:06:03.549">*You have to remember, <br/>it was 1928 I was born.*</p>
      <p begin="00:06:03.549" end="00:06:08.931">*So in '30, '31, the Depression was on.*</p>
      <p begin="00:06:08.931" end="00:06:12.086">*My father left us. Had a young brother.*</p>
      <p begin="00:06:12.086" end="00:06:14.454">And unlike today, <br/>where we're multi-cultural,</p>
      <p begin="00:06:16.954" end="00:06:17.954">being Jewish, we stood out in those days.</p>
      <p begin="00:06:17.954" end="00:06:20.638">*We needed somewhere to live.*</p>
      <p begin="00:06:20.638" end="00:06:25.826">So, she appealed to the Jewish authorities<br/>to take us into this orphanage here.</p>
      <p begin="00:06:25.826" end="00:06:31.106">And I spent from five to eleven<br/>in the orphanage,</p>
      <p begin="00:06:31.106" end="00:06:34.849">and sang in the synagogue choir.</p>
      <p begin="00:06:34.849" end="00:06:53.465">&#9834; [music] &#9834;</p>
      <p begin="00:06:53.465" end="00:06:58.092">Hmmm</p>
      <p begin="00:06:58.092" end="00:07:03.711">Seventy two years ago, <br/>this is where I used to sit.</p>
      <p begin="00:07:03.711" end="00:07:05.786">I was a choir boy.</p>
      <p begin="00:07:05.786" end="00:07:11.596">The choir master, <br/>he'd rap my knuckles on occasion.</p>
      <p begin="00:07:11.596" end="00:07:13.507">[laughs]</p>
      <p begin="00:07:13.507" end="00:07:16.998">'Cause, you know, we were kids<br/>and we were naughty at times.</p>
      <p begin="00:07:16.998" end="00:07:21.015">*But they were charming services.<br/>they were very warm, very gentle.*</p>
      <p begin="00:07:21.461" end="00:07:25.497">*Right now, at this moment,*</p>
      <p begin="00:07:25.497" end="00:07:28.241">I don't know if I did then &#8211; <br/>I was far too young.</p>
      <p begin="00:07:28.241" end="00:07:31.463">But right now, I'm feeling all spiritual.</p>
      <p begin="00:07:31.463" end="00:07:38.840">There's a sense of peace here <br/>and it's a wonderful-shaped synagogue.</p>
      <p begin="00:07:38.840" end="00:07:43.751">*It hasn't changed. <br/>I can't think of anything that's changed.*</p>
      <p begin="00:07:43.751" end="00:07:48.110">To give you just a few bars<br/>of something that we used to sing,</p>
      <p begin="00:07:48.110" end="00:07:50.265">we used to go *Hallelujah, Hallelujah.*</p>
      <p begin="00:07:50.265" end="00:07:53.585">And the tune was<br/>&#9834; [Hallelujah] &#9834;</p>
      <p begin="00:07:53.585" end="00:07:55.728">*&#9834; [Hallelujah] &#9834; *</p>
      <p begin="00:07:55.728" end="00:08:08.647">[singing continues]</p>
      <p begin="00:08:08.647" end="00:08:10.601">*What I miss most is my mom.*</p>
      <p begin="00:08:10.601" end="00:08:17.957">*They only allowed me to see her<br/>once a month.*</p>
      <p begin="00:08:17.957" end="00:08:20.979">*I ran away from the orphanage.*</p>
      <p begin="00:08:20.979" end="00:08:25.381">*Went to my dad which is so much closer<br/>than the East End where my mother lived.*</p>
      <p begin="00:08:25.381" end="00:08:30.142">*He got me back to the orphanage<br/>as quick as he could.*</p>
      <p begin="00:08:30.142" end="00:08:33.861">*And I could see that <br/>there was no caring or love.*</p>
      <p begin="00:08:33.861" end="00:08:39.741">* You could tell that as he walked away,<br/>when he passed me over to the authorities,*</p>
      <p begin="00:08:39.741" end="00:08:42.659">*that he already had <br/>something else on his mind.*</p>
      <p begin="00:08:42.659" end="00:08:45.330">*He didn't even look at me.*</p>
      <p begin="00:08:45.330" end="00:08:52.534">And I think that moment, was when I lost <br/>any love that I had for him.</p>
      <p begin="00:08:52.534" end="00:08:55.314">Never saw him again.</p>
      <p begin="00:08:55.945" end="00:08:59.089">- [Betty Sassoon] You see, <br/>I had two beautiful sons.</p>
      <p begin="00:08:59.089" end="00:09:00.734">And I'd always had that feeling</p>
      <p begin="00:09:00.734" end="00:09:05.987">that I wanted my sons to grow up<br/>to be very proud of their mother.</p>
      <p begin="00:09:05.987" end="00:09:08.415">And think that helped me an awful lot.</p>
      <p begin="00:09:08.415" end="00:09:12.657">- If there's anything you'd wish for me<br/>in the future, what would it be?</p>
      <p begin="00:09:12.657" end="00:09:14.457">- Oh, God, and this is the truth...</p>
      <p begin="00:09:14.457" end="00:09:19.299">I wish happiness in your life<br/>because you deserve it, son.</p>
      <p begin="00:09:19.299" end="00:09:21.967">If anybody deserves it,<br/>that's you because you've been&#8230;</p>
      <p begin="00:09:21.967" end="00:09:24.010">to me...</p>
      <p begin="00:09:24.010" end="00:09:27.559">Please, It&#8217;s the truth the best son <br/>a mother could ever have.</p>
      <p begin="00:09:27.559" end="00:09:34.672">And I think I am blessed by God<br/>to have such a son.</p>
      <p begin="00:09:34.672" end="00:09:36.727">*- [Vidal] Her life was a painful one.*</p>
      <p begin="00:09:36.727" end="00:09:40.618">*Mine was different. I knew nothing else.<br/>The orphanage and then the war broke out.*</p>
      <p begin="00:09:40.618" end="00:09:45.086">*- [Churchill] We can go on to the end.<br/>We can fight in France.*</p>
      <p begin="00:09:45.086" end="00:09:47.132">*We can fight on the seas and oceans.*</p>
      <p begin="00:09:47.132" end="00:09:49.235">- *[Vidal] And then suddenly, <br/>we were all picked-up.*</p>
      <p begin="00:09:49.235" end="00:09:52.978">*All the kids of London <br/>and sent to the country.*</p>
      <p begin="00:09:52.978" end="00:09:55.983">*Where we lived with cows and sheep <br/>for the next few years.*</p>
      <p begin="00:09:55.983" end="00:09:58.041">And of course very nice people <br/>that took us in.</p>
      <p begin="00:09:58.041" end="00:10:01.628">I came back to London at fourteen<br/>and the war was still on.</p>
      <p begin="00:10:01.628" end="00:10:05.563">*And we were sleeping down the shelter<br/>as everybody did.*</p>
      <p begin="00:10:05.563" end="00:10:10.167">*And the Luftwaffe was rearranging<br/>the streets of London every night.*</p>
      <p begin="00:10:10.167" end="00:10:12.416">*The architecture was changing <br/>at every moment.*</p>
      <p begin="00:10:12.416" end="00:10:15.878">-*[Churchill] We shall defend our island<br/>whatever the cost may be.*</p>
      <p begin="00:10:15.878" end="00:10:18.199">- *[Vidal] I had a job as a glove cutter.*</p>
      <p begin="00:10:18.199" end="00:10:20.008">*I was cutting the little snippets*</p>
      <p begin="00:10:20.008" end="00:10:23.186">*that they would sew the gloves<br/>together with.*</p>
      <p begin="00:10:23.186" end="00:10:24.884">*It seemed I always had <br/>a pair of shears in my hand.*</p>
      <p begin="00:10:24.884" end="00:10:27.522">*Except for three months in London.*</p>
      <p begin="00:10:27.522" end="00:10:31.381">*They needed messenger boys who had bikes*</p>
      <p begin="00:10:31.381" end="00:10:35.729">*to take messages from<br/>the city to the darks.*</p>
      <p begin="00:10:35.729" end="00:10:39.898">*My mother had remarried Nathan G., <br/>Nathan Goldberg.*</p>
      <p begin="00:10:39.898" end="00:10:43.809">*Great guy. <br/>He got me a bike and I got the job.*</p>
      <p begin="00:10:43.809" end="00:10:45.058">*The job was fascinating*</p>
      <p begin="00:10:45.058" end="00:10:48.877">*because the streets were blocked<br/>and buildings were down.*</p>
      <p begin="00:10:48.877" end="00:10:53.360">*And I was riding this bike at fourteen, <br/>really having fun.*</p>
      <p begin="00:10:53.360" end="00:10:54.377">[explosions]</p>
      <p begin="00:10:54.377" end="00:10:56.643">*You know you began to feel<br/>like a war hero.* <span tts:fontStyle="italic">[chuckles]</span></p>
      <p begin="00:10:56.643" end="00:10:58.151">[crowd cheering]</p>
      <p begin="00:10:58.151" end="00:11:01.205">- [Churchill] ...and in the streets, <br/>we'll fight in the hills.</p>
      <p begin="00:11:01.205" end="00:11:03.686">We shall never surrender.</p>
      <p begin="00:11:03.686" end="00:11:08.047">*My mother, she was always concerned,<br/>saying, "You gotta learn a trade!"*</p>
      <p begin="00:11:08.047" end="00:11:11.124">*She said, "Well, I've had a premonition."*</p>
      <p begin="00:11:11.124" end="00:11:11.995">*"What's that mother?"*</p>
      <p begin="00:11:11.995" end="00:11:14.574">*She said, <br/>"You're going to be a hairdresser."*</p>
      <p begin="00:11:14.574" end="00:11:16.489">*I said,<br/>[whispers] "I'm going to be what?"*</p>
      <p begin="00:11:16.489" end="00:11:18.957">*She said, "A hairdresser."*</p>
      <p begin="00:11:18.957" end="00:11:21.463">*So she walked me by the hand.*</p>
      <p begin="00:11:21.463" end="00:11:24.410">*Into a man called Adolph Cohen,<br/>in White Chapel Road.*</p>
      <p begin="00:11:24.410" end="00:11:26.513">* Now, White Chapel <br/>is the heart of the ghetto.*</p>
      <p begin="00:11:26.513" end="00:11:28.050">*And there was this wonderful<br/>little man.*</p>
      <p begin="00:11:28.050" end="00:11:30.013">*He couldn't have been more than five feet.*</p>
      <p begin="00:11:30.013" end="00:11:32.720">He asked for a hundred guinnes.</p>
      <p begin="00:11:32.720" end="00:11:38.118">Now that was a a hundred pounds <br/>and a hundred shillings in those days.</p>
      <p begin="00:11:38.118" end="00:11:40.768">Which is an impossible figure.</p>
      <p begin="00:11:40.768" end="00:11:43.511">My mother said, "We don't have <br/>a hundred buttons."</p>
      <p begin="00:11:43.511" end="00:11:49.200">I was kinda smiling because I was relieved<br/>I wasn't going to be a hairdresser.</p>
      <p begin="00:11:49.200" end="00:11:51.946">So I went to the door <br/>and opened it for my mother</p>
      <p begin="00:11:51.946" end="00:11:53.557">*and ushered her through.*</p>
      <p begin="00:11:53.557" end="00:11:55.944">*And I doffed the cap.<br/>He followed us out.*</p>
      <p begin="00:11:55.944" end="00:11:58.832">He said "You seem to have rather <br/>good manners, young man."</p>
      <p begin="00:11:58.832" end="00:12:03.948">"Start Monday." He looked at my mom <br/>and said, "Let's forget the fee."</p>
      <p begin="00:12:03.948" end="00:12:06.317">So my apprenticeship cost nothing.</p>
      <p begin="00:12:06.317" end="00:12:14.434">&#9834; [music] &#9834;</p>
      <p begin="00:12:14.434" end="00:12:17.436">*I was apprentice for two years <br/>with Adolph.*</p>
      <p begin="00:12:17.436" end="00:12:19.401">*Extraordinary man.*</p>
      <p begin="00:12:19.401" end="00:12:23.412">*Pressed trousers every morning.<br/>Clean nails. Clean Shoes.*</p>
      <p begin="00:12:23.412" end="00:12:26.277">Middle of a war --<br/>how was that possible?</p>
      <p begin="00:12:26.277" end="00:12:27.959">He was a disciplinarian!</p>
      <p begin="00:12:27.959" end="00:12:34.267">And i think that had<br/>an enormous effect on my sense of how</p>
